Defendant in custody.
The Court sentences the defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of sixty (60) months.  That is thirty (30) months initial confinement followed by thirty (30) months extended supervision.
The defendant is found eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) Maintain fulltime employment or school combination;
5) Pay court costs including $150.00 buy money to Metro Drug Unit;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
The defendant has credit for 293 days.
Minutes.

Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Maintain full-time work or school combination;
5) Spend eight (8) months in the Manitowoc County Jail, under the Huber Law, to commence on 12-22-15 by 8:00 a.m.  Transfer to Juneau County Jail is authorized.  
6) Repay $150.00 buy money to Metro Drug Unit;
7) Submit a DNA sample and pay surcharge;
8) Pay costs of action including $873.02 in jury fees;
9) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.   
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.   
Minutes.
